Flaminius was consul 223, and led the legions across the Po to attack the Insubres. Polyb. 11. 32 accuses him of bad strategy, though the Gauls were routed. Meantime the senate mistrusting his rashness, or alarmed by omens, sent to recall him, on the ground of the sentence of the augurs consules vitio creatos. Fl. would not open the despatches till the battle was over, and refused to abdicate. On his return· the senate would not allow him a public triumph, but he entered the city in triumphal procession despite their refusal.
